Categorical Variables in Bar Charts

A quick look at counts of the various levels of the categorical variables found in the data is shown in the following set of bar charts. Trelliscopejs is an R package that enables one to quickly sort and/or filter through various slices (or features) of their previously generated visualizations/plots of their data. We can then sort and filter through the feature set to find anomalies or interesting behaviors that might influence modeling or help us understand basic relationships between variables in the data.

For this dataset the number of categorical variables is not overwhelming so the power of trelliscope would appear limited. However, when one needs to quickly move through 100s, 1000s or even millions of slices of the data, trelliscope provides a seemless interface to manage so many subsets of data and better discover interesting features.
